    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      535.63,
      564.76,
      547.63
    ],
    "text": "When the said plaint was filed before the District Court of Kalmunai on 18.11.2004 by the Appellant,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      564.91,
      564.79,
      576.91
    ],
    "text": "the Respondent filed his answer on 04.05.2005. The case proceeded to trial on 29 issues, of which 23",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      594.22,
      364.1,
      606.22
    ],
    "text": "were suggested by the Appellant and 06 by the Respondent.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      633.46,
      565.21,
      645.46
    ],
    "text": "After trial the learned Additional District Judge Kalmunai dismissed the action of the Appellant as",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      662.86,
      565.0,
      674.86
    ],
    "text": "well as the claim in reconvention of the Respondent. Being dissatisfied by the said decision, both the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      692.14,
      565.06,
      704.14
    ],
    "text": "Appellant as well as the Respondent preferred two appeals to the Provincial High Court of Civil",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 1,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      721.42,
      226.2,
      733.42
    ],
    "text": "Appeal of the Eastern Province.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      38.16,
      565.16,
      77.28
    ],
    "text": "3 The Provincial High Court of Civil Appeal, by its Judgment dated 02.07.2014 dismissed both Appeals",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      94.58,
      565.22,
      106.58
    ],
    "text": "and affirmed the judgment of the District Court. The Appellant preferred a leave to appeal",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      123.86,
      564.8,
      135.86
    ],
    "text": "application against the said decision of the Provincial High Court of Civil Appeal. The Supreme Court",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      153.14,
      564.79,
      165.14
    ],
    "text": "after considering the submissions made by the both parties, granted leave, on the questions of law",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      182.42,
      565.05,
      194.42
    ],
    "text": "raised in sub-paragraphs (a) to (d) and (i) of paragraph 14 of the petition dated 13.08.2014 and an",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      211.7,
      447.38,
      223.7
    ],
    "text": "additional ground of Appeal raised on behalf of the Respondent to the effect;",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      251.09,
      565.01,
      263.09
    ],
    "text": "\u201cEven the document marked as P-7 is admitted in evidence, has the Plaintiff proved his title to",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      280.37,
      542.33,
      292.37
    ],
    "text": "the land in dispute in view of the transfer effected by deed No. 13486 dated 30.06.1988.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      319.73,
      565.29,
      331.73
    ],
    "text": "When going through the issues under which the leave was granted to the Appellant, it appears that",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      349.01,
      565.21,
      361.01
    ],
    "text": "the entire case before this court was based on the failure by the Plaintiff to lead in evidence the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      378.29,
      461.93,
      390.29
    ],
    "text": "documents which were produced during the District Court Trial subject to proof.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      417.55,
      564.85,
      429.55
    ],
    "text": "The plaintiff\u2019s action before the District Court of Kalmunai was for the declaration of title, and the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      446.83,
      565.17,
      458.83
    ],
    "text": "plaintiff had relied his title on deed No. 2119, which was marked as P-7. When establishing the title,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      476.23,
      564.9,
      488.23
    ],
    "text": "in a rei vindicatio action the Plaintiff should set out his title on the basis on which he claims a",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      505.51,
      478.61,
      517.51
    ],
    "text": "declaration of title to the land and the proof required is the standard of strict proof.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      544.75,
      565.19,
      556.75
    ],
    "text": "The above position was discussed in a series of decisions both in the Court of Appeal and the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      574.06,
      565.36,
      586.06
    ],
    "text": "Supreme Court including the decisions in Wanigaratne Vs. Juwanis Appuhamy 65 NLR 167 and",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-BoldItalic",
      "Calibri-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      603.46,
      298.08,
      615.46
    ],
    "text": "Dharmadasa Vs. Jayasena [1997] 3 Sri LR 327.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      642.7,
      565.17,
      654.7
    ],
    "text": "In the case of P.D.C. Perera Vs. K.J Perera SC Appeal 95/2003 SC minute dated 08.12.2005 Supreme",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      671.98,
      130.05,
      683.98
    ],
    "text": "Court held,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      711.34,
      565.28,
      723.34
    ],
    "text": "\u201cThus it would be clear that the plaintiff in a rei vindicatio action can base his claim for relief",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 2,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      740.64,
      340.94,
      752.64
    ],
    "text": "on either of the two alternative grounds namely",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      38.16,
      565.16,
      62.64
    ],
    "text": "4",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      135.14,
      63.42,
      479.09,
      77.28
    ],
    "text": "1) He can claim relief on the ground that he has a valid paper title or,",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      135.14,
      92.72,
      443.42,
      106.58
    ],
    "text": "2) He can rely on the ground of simple possession and ouster",
    "fonts": [
      "ArialMT",
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      133.82,
      565.36,
      145.82
    ],
    "text": "As submitted above, the Appellant relied in his title on the deed produced marked P-7 and when the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      163.22,
      565.36,
      175.22
    ],
    "text": "said deed was produced, Respondent had objected for the said deed but, when the Plaintiff",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      192.5,
      565.37,
      204.5
    ],
    "text": "(Appellant) closed its case without calling any witness to prove P-7 before the District Court the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      221.78,
      564.91,
      233.78
    ],
    "text": "Defendant (Respondent) did not raise any specific objection for the failure by the Appellant. In this",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      251.09,
      565.0,
      263.09
    ],
    "text": "regard the Appellant took up the position that, it was clear from the above conduct of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      280.37,
      565.37,
      292.37
    ],
    "text": "Respondent that, the Respondent did not intend to pursue the \u201cpro forma\u201d objections raised by him",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      309.65,
      245.76,
      321.65
    ],
    "text": "and thereby waved such objections.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      349.01,
      565.17,
      361.01
    ],
    "text": "However as observed above in this judgment, the appellant in this case has claimed relief purely on",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      378.29,
      565.31,
      390.29
    ],
    "text": "the basis of paper title, i.e. on the title the appellant claimed through deed No. 2119. He has a duty",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      407.59,
      564.8,
      419.59
    ],
    "text": "to prove the document as required by law for a Court of law to act upon such deed. In this regard this",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      436.87,
      564.88,
      448.87
    ],
    "text": "court is mindful of the requirement under section 68 of the Evidence Ordinance which reads as",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      466.15,
      108.57,
      478.15
    ],
    "text": "follows;",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      505.51,
      564.96,
      517.51
    ],
    "text": "Section 68; If a document is required by law to be attested, it should not be used as",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      175.58,
      534.79,
      565.35,
      546.79
    ],
    "text": "evidence until one attesting witness at least has been called for the purpose of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      175.58,
      564.07,
      564.9,
      576.07
    ],
    "text": "proving its execution, if there be an attesting witness alive, and subject to the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      175.58,
      593.38,
      428.06,
      605.38
    ],
    "text": "process of the court and capable of giving evidence",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      632.74,
      565.21,
      644.74
    ],
    "text": "Section 70 of the Evidence Ordinance which is the only exception to the above rule, referred to an",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      662.02,
      370.58,
      674.02
    ],
    "text": "admission recorded with regard to such document as follows;",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      38.16,
      565.16,
      62.64
    ],
    "text": "5",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      65.28,
      564.92,
      77.28
    ],
    "text": "Section 70; The admission of a party to an attested document or its execution by himself",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      175.58,
      94.58,
      564.87,
      106.58
    ],
    "text": "shall be sufficient proof of its execution as against him, though it be a",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      175.58,
      123.86,
      378.62,
      135.86
    ],
    "text": "document required by law to be attested",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      163.22,
      564.94,
      175.22
    ],
    "text": "However in the absence of any written admission recorded at the District Court Trial and an",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      192.5,
      564.82,
      204.5
    ],
    "text": "objection recorded when the document was initially produced, it is difficult for this court to ignore",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      221.78,
      565.37,
      233.78
    ],
    "text": "the provisions of section 68 of the Evidence Ordinance, even though no specific objection was raised,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      251.09,
      447.02,
      263.09
    ],
    "text": "when the Plaintiff closed his case producing several documents including P-7.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      290.33,
      567.41,
      302.33
    ],
    "text": "In this regard the appellant heavily relied on the following passage by Samarakoon CJ in the case of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      319.73,
      398.66,
      331.73
    ],
    "text": "Sri Lanka Ports Authority V. Jugolinija -Boal East [1981] 1 Sri LR 18",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri-BoldItalic",
      "Calibri-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      358.97,
      565.35,
      370.97
    ],
    "text": "\u201cIf no objection is taken, when at the close of a case documents are read in the evidence, they",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      388.25,
      559.01,
      400.25
    ],
    "text": "are evidence for all purposes of the law. This is the \u2018cursus curiae\u2019 of the original civil courts.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      427.63,
      565.08,
      439.63
    ],
    "text": "As further submitted by the Appellant, the above decision was followed by the Supreme Court in the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      456.91,
      558.17,
      468.91
    ],
    "text": "case of Balapitiye Gunananda Thero Vs. Thalalle Methananda Thero [1997] II Sri LR 101 as follows;",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      496.15,
      564.87,
      508.15
    ],
    "text": "\u201cWhen a document is admitted subject to proof but when tendered and read in evidence at",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      525.43,
      564.82,
      537.43
    ],
    "text": "the close of the case is accepted without objection, it becomes evidence in the case. This is",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      554.83,
      196.8,
      566.83
    ],
    "text": "the cursus curiae.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      594.1,
      565.11,
      606.1
    ],
    "text": "However, none of the above cases referred to a document which required by law to be attested, and",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      623.38,
      565.37,
      635.38
    ],
    "text": "in the said circumstances, provisions in section 68 of the Evidence Ordinance has no applicability to",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      652.66,
      278.04,
      664.66
    ],
    "text": "the situations referred to in the said cases.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      692.02,
      565.17,
      704.02
    ],
    "text": "Section 31 of the Notaries Ordinance required a Notarially executed deed to carry an attestation with",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      721.3,
      565.08,
      733.3
    ],
    "text": "two attesting witnesses and in the said circumstances it is necessary to follow the provisions of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      38.16,
      565.16,
      77.28
    ],
    "text": "6 section 68 of the Evidence Ordinance, in the absence of an admission under section 70 of the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      94.58,
      170.25,
      106.58
    ],
    "text": "Evidence Ordinance.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      133.82,
      565.35,
      145.82
    ],
    "text": "During the argument before us the Petitioner further relied on the decision in Samarakoon Vs.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      163.22,
      549.89,
      175.22
    ],
    "text": "Gunasekera and Another reported in [2011] I Sri LR 149 where Amaratunga J observed as follows;",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri",
      "Calibri-BoldItalic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      202.46,
      565.22,
      214.46
    ],
    "text": "3. \u201cWhen a document is admitted subject to proof, the party tendering it in evidence is",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      139.58,
      231.74,
      564.93,
      243.74
    ],
    "text": "obliged to formally prove it by calling the evidence necessary to prove the document",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      139.58,
      261.05,
      565.03,
      273.05
    ],
    "text": "according to law. If such evidence is not called and if no objection is taken to the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      139.58,
      290.33,
      565.22,
      302.33
    ],
    "text": "document when it is read in evidence at the time of closing the case of the party who",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      139.58,
      319.73,
      424.34,
      331.73
    ],
    "text": "tendered the document it becomes evidence in the cases.",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      358.97,
      564.85,
      370.97
    ],
    "text": "4. On the other hand if the document is objected to at the time when it is read in",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      139.58,
      388.25,
      564.88,
      400.25
    ],
    "text": "evidence before closing the case of the party who tendered the document in",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      139.58,
      417.55,
      529.85,
      429.55
    ],
    "text": "evidence, the document cannot be used as evidence for the party tendering it.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      456.91,
      564.89,
      468.91
    ],
    "text": "However as observed by this court Amaratunga J was mindful of the requirement under section 68 of",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      486.19,
      312.84,
      498.19
    ],
    "text": "the Evidence Ordinance when he concluded that,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      525.43,
      565.08,
      537.43
    ],
    "text": "\u201cA deed for sale or transfer of land, being a document which is required by law to be attested,",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      554.83,
      564.84,
      566.83
    ],
    "text": "has to be proved in the manner set out in section 68 of the Evidence Ordinance by proof that",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      584.14,
      564.85,
      596.14
    ],
    "text": "the maker (the vendor) of that document signed it in the presence of witnesses and the",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      103.58,
      613.42,
      524.45,
      625.42
    ],
    "text": "notary. If this is not done the document and its contents cannot be used in evidence.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      652.66,
      564.78,
      664.66
    ],
    "text": "When the present application was supported before this court for notices, the Respondent too had",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      681.94,
      565.36,
      693.94
    ],
    "text": "moved to add an additional ground of Appeal and the attention was drawn by the Respondent to an",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      67.58,
      711.34,
      564.85,
      723.34
    ],
    "text": "endorsement made on the Original Deed No. 24680 during the arguments before this court. As",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
